<div align="center"><h2><xar:mlstring>Authinvision Module Overview</xar:mlstring></h2></div><br />
<table border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td align="left" valign="top" width="100px">
            <b><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></b>
        </td>
        <td align="left" valign="top">
            <p><xar:mlstring>The Authinvision module allows you to authenticate a user with your Invision Board database.  The Authinvision module checks the username and password from the login screen against the Invision database and returns true for a match.</xar:mlstring></p>
            <p><xar:mlstring>Authinvision <strong>does not</strong> log users into both systems at once, nor does it allow users who register on xaraya to have their user information duplicated in the Invision database.  <strong>It is highly suggested that you turn off xaraya registration and use your Invision board's registration/password retrieval process.</strong></xar:mlstring></p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td align="left" valign="top" width="100px">
            <b><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></b>
        </td>
        <td align="left" valign="top">
            <xar:mlstring>Authentication by Authinvision is automatically set once the the Authinvision module has been initialized.   You must configure Authinvision before a user will be able to login to Xaraya.  To remove Authinvision authentication, you must remove the module.</xar:mlstring>
            <br /><br />
            <xar:mlstring>
            From the menu, you have one choice.  "Modify Config". 
            </xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Modify Config -- From here, you can configure the authinvision server that will be used for authentication.   A user that has account information in Invision to be automatically added to the Xaraya database and allowed to login.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td align="left" valign="top" width="100px">
            <b><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></b>
        </td>
        <td align="left" valign="top">
            <xar:mlstring>usercp: a block that mimics the user links from Invision.</xar:mlstring><br/>
      <xar:mlstring>whos_online.php: a who's online block that replaces the one in the roles module.</xar:mlstring>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
